============================================================
CONFIG REQUIREMENTS
============================================================

Update `.env.example` with:

CONTENT_PIPELINE_ENABLED=true
CONTENT_STORE=in_memory

EDITOR_AGENT_ENABLED=true
GRAPHIC_AGENT_ENABLED=true
SOCIAL_AGENT_ENABLED=true

CONTENT_DEFAULT_BRAND=zDash
CONTENT_DEFAULT_LANGUAGE=en
CONTENT_DEFAULT_TONE=professional
CONTENT_REQUIRE_POLICY_CHECK=true

IMAGE_GENERATION_PROVIDER=mock
IMAGE_DRY_RUN=true
IMAGE_OUTPUT_DIR=backend/data/content/images

SOCIAL_PROVIDER=mock
SOCIAL_DRY_RUN=true
SOCIAL_APPROVAL_REQUIRED=true
SOCIAL_AUTO_POST_ENABLED=false
SOCIAL_DEFAULT_PLATFORMS=x,tiktok,facebook,instagram,linkedin

SOCIAL_X_API_KEY=
SOCIAL_X_API_SECRET=
SOCIAL_TIKTOK_ACCESS_TOKEN=
SOCIAL_FACEBOOK_ACCESS_TOKEN=
SOCIAL_INSTAGRAM_ACCESS_TOKEN=
SOCIAL_LINKEDIN_ACCESS_TOKEN=

Rules:

- Missing config must fail safely.
- Mock providers must work without external credentials.
- Social posting must default to dry-run.
- Auto-post must be disabled by default.
- Approval must be required by default.
- Real posting requires:
  - SOCIAL_DRY_RUN=false
  - SOCIAL_AUTO_POST_ENABLED=true
  - SOCIAL_APPROVAL_REQUIRED=false or item status approved
  - valid platform token
  - policy check passed

============================================================
CONTENT MODEL REQUIREMENTS
============================================================

Create Pydantic models in:

backend/app/content/models.py

Models:

1. ContentStatus

Allowed values:
- draft
- edited
- graphic_requested
- graphic_ready
- scheduled
- approved
- posted
- failed
- rejected

2. ContentPlatform

Allowed values:
- x
- tiktok
- facebook
- instagram
- linkedin
- blog
- generic

3. ContentType

Allowed values:
- text_post
- image_post
- short_video_script
- thread
- blog_outline
- announcement
- market_note
- educational

4. ContentItem

Fields:
- id: str
- title: str
- content_type: ContentType
- status: ContentStatus
- brand: str
- language: str
- tone: str
- topic: str
- draft_text: str | None
- edited_text: str | None
- graphic_prompt: str | None
- graphic_asset_url: str | None
- platforms: list[ContentPlatform]
- scheduled_at: datetime | None
- approved_at: datetime | None
- posted_at: datetime | None
- policy_passed: bool
- policy_notes: list[str]
- metadata: dict
- created_at: datetime
- updated_at: datetime

5. CreateContentRequest

Fields:
- topic: str
- content_type: ContentType = "text_post"
- brand: str | None = None
- language: str | None = None
- tone: str | None = None
- platforms: list[ContentPlatform] = ["generic"]
- context: dict = {}

Validation:
- topic must not be empty
- platforms must not be empty

6. EditContentRequest

Fields:
- content_id: str
- instructions: str | None = None
- tone: str | None = None
- language: str | None = None

7. GraphicRequest

Fields:
- content_id: str
- style: str = "clean professional dashboard visual"
- aspect_ratio: str = "16:9"
- instructions: str | None = None

8. ScheduleContentRequest

Fields:
- content_id: str
- scheduled_at: datetime
- platforms: list[ContentPlatform] | None = None

9. ApproveContentRequest

Fields:
- content_id: str
- approved_by: str = "operator"
- notes: str | None = None

10. PublishContentRequest

Fields:
- content_id: str
- platforms: list[ContentPlatform] | None = None
- confirmation: bool = false

11. SocialPostResult

Fields:
- platform: ContentPlatform
- ok: bool
- dry_run: bool
- external_id: str | None
- message: str
- output: dict
- timestamp: datetime

12. PipelineRunResult

Fields:
- id: str
- content_id: str
- ok: bool
- status: ContentStatus
- steps: list[dict]
- message: str
- started_at: datetime
- finished_at: datetime
- duration_ms: int

============================================================
CONTENT STORE REQUIREMENTS
============================================================

Create:

backend/app/content/store.py

Implement:

InMemoryContentStore

Methods:

- create_item(request: CreateContentRequest) -> ContentItem
- get_item(content_id: str) -> ContentItem | None
- list_items(status: ContentStatus | None = None) -> list[ContentItem]
- update_item(content_id: str, patch: dict) -> ContentItem
- delete_item(content_id: str) -> bool
- record_pipeline_run(result: PipelineRunResult) -> PipelineRunResult
- list_pipeline_runs(content_id: str | None = None) -> list[PipelineRunResult]

Rules:

- Use UUID for content item IDs.
- Store content in memory for Phase 6.
- Design for future database persistence.
- Do not crash on missing item; raise clean domain error.
- Always update updated_at on mutation.

============================================================
CONTENT POLICY REQUIREMENTS
============================================================

Create:

backend/app/content/policy.py

Implement:

ContentPolicyChecker

Method:

- check_text(text: str, context: dict | None = None) -> dict

Return:

{
  "passed": true,
  "notes": [],
  "blocked_terms": [],
  "warnings": []
}

Policy checks:

- Reject empty content.
- Reject obvious credential leakage patterns:
  - API keys
  - access tokens
  - passwords
  - private keys
- Reject misleading guaranteed-profit language.
- Reject impersonation language.
- Reject spam patterns:
  - excessive repeated hashtags
  - excessive emojis
  - repeated links
- Warn if the content mentions trading or market results.
- Warn if post lacks educational or risk disclaimer when discussing strategy/backtesting/trading.

Rules:

- Keep policy deterministic.
- Do not call external APIs.
- Policy checker must be conservative.
- Policy failure blocks approval and publishing.

============================================================
EDITOR SERVICE REQUIREMENTS
============================================================

Create:

backend/app/content/editor_service.py

Implement:

EditorService

Methods:

- create_draft(request: CreateContentRequest) -> ContentItem
- edit_content(request: EditContentRequest) -> ContentItem
- generate_variants(content_id: str, count: int = 3) -> list[str]

Behavior:

- Uses AI adapter if available.
- Falls back to deterministic mock text if AI is unavailable.
- Draft text should be generated from topic, brand, tone, language, and content_type.
- Edited text should be concise, readable, and platform-safe.
- For trading-related content, add educational/simulation disclaimer.
- Emits events:
  - content.draft.created
  - content.edited
  - content.variant.generated
  - content.policy.checked
  - content.policy.failed

