============================================================
SOCIAL SERVICE REQUIREMENTS
============================================================

Create:

backend/app/content/social_service.py

Implement:

SocialService

Methods:

- schedule_content(request: ScheduleContentRequest) -> ContentItem
- approve_content(request: ApproveContentRequest) -> ContentItem
- publish_content(request: PublishContentRequest) -> list[SocialPostResult]

Behavior:

- Approval requires policy_passed=true.
- Publish requires:
  - item exists
  - item status approved or SOCIAL_APPROVAL_REQUIRED=false
  - policy_passed=true
  - SOCIAL_DRY_RUN=true or confirmation=true
- In dry-run mode, simulate posting and return mock external IDs.
- In real mode, use SocialMediaAdapter.
- Never publish rejected or failed content.
- Emits events:
  - content.scheduled
  - content.approved
  - content.rejected
  - content.publish.requested
  - content.publish.simulated
  - content.published
  - content.publish.blocked
  - content.publish.failed

