============================================================
PIPELINE REQUIREMENTS
============================================================

Create:

backend/app/content/pipeline.py

Implement:

ContentPipeline

Methods:

- run_full_pipeline(request: CreateContentRequest) -> PipelineRunResult
- create_then_edit(request: CreateContentRequest) -> PipelineRunResult
- generate_graphic(content_id: str) -> PipelineRunResult
- schedule(content_id: str, scheduled_at: datetime, platforms: list[ContentPlatform] | None = None) -> PipelineRunResult
- approve(content_id: str, approved_by: str = "operator") -> PipelineRunResult
- publish(content_id: str, platforms: list[ContentPlatform] | None = None, confirmation: bool = false) -> PipelineRunResult

Full pipeline order:

1. Create draft
2. Edit content
3. Run policy check
4. Generate graphic prompt
5. Generate mock graphic
6. Do not approve automatically
7. Do not publish automatically

Rules:

- Pipeline must stop on policy failure.
- Pipeline must not auto-publish.
- Pipeline must record each step.
- Pipeline must emit start/completed/failed events.
- Failures must be captured in PipelineRunResult.

Events:

- content.pipeline.started
- content.pipeline.step.completed
- content.pipeline.completed
- content.pipeline.failed

